\\\":\\\"**Clarifying dynamic access**\\\\n\\\\nI’m trying to figure out dynamic access in the context of `build/native/nativeTestCompile/reflection-calls` during JVM testing. I wonder if an agent might be involved, but I'm not sure. Adding a reference like `logger instanceof org.slf4j.impl.Log4jLoggerAdapter` could lead to early class loading. Importing and referencing a class literal might trigger it as well, which isn’t necessary since the test uses the class directly. \\\\n\\\\nI think calling `Class#forName` on `Log4jLoggerAdapter.class$` only happens if the class literal is evaluated, but that involves considering if it's compile-time or runtime.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating class structure**\\\\n\\\\nI've got one active class, but the idea of \\\\\\\"one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files\\\\\\\" suggests that each generated test class file should be dedicated. It doesn't completely rule out using a placeholder, though. I wonder if making the placeholder public is needed; it might not be necessary. I'll need to check the style and see if the tests use a package based on group or artifact.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_r8PZGdxzuRuokteRCyhKeEME|fc_0a0399cef038036a0169f570c9f740819fb5f6de954ce9e7e1\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find tests/src -path '*/src/test/java/*AdapterTest.java' -o -path '*/src/test/java/*Logger*Test.java' | head -20\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 478, \"output\": 1355, \"cacheRead\": 13824, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 15657, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777692853095, \"responseId\": \"resp_0a0399cef038036a0169f570b56c30819f9eed465062de1930\"}}\n1084:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying dynamic access**\\n\\nI’m trying to figure out dynamic access in the context of `build/native/nativeTestCompile/reflection-calls` during JVM testing. I wonder if an agent might be involved, but I'm not sure. Adding a reference like `logger instanceof org.slf4j.impl.Log4jLoggerAdapter` could lead to early class loading. Importing and referencing a class literal might trigger it as well, which isn’t necessary since the test uses the class directly. \\n\\nI think calling `Class#forName` on `Log4jLoggerAdapter.class$` only happens if the class literal is evaluated, but that involves considering if it's compile-time or runtime.\\n\\n**Evaluating class structure**\\n\\nI've got one active class, but the idea of \\\"one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files\\\" suggests that each generated test class file should be dedicated. It doesn't completely rule out using a placeholder, though. I wonder if making the placeholder public is needed; it might not be necessary. I'll need to check the style and see if the tests use a package based on group or artifact.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0a0399cef038036a0169f570b5e8bc819f96d55876ea7c3ebf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9XDJ5mRE8mPMVW8VRcYeoMsVoJzPeWMyYW_kXIaZZo6KfAwdwjiQRpLo4ZtuIrNLfZgPvwz693oErqmDT3M9OWoKzSI6f5n3rErTkbhPhyUqaHEh-3drmEM-VAX3ZvFBdP73OoGs2qLQ9sQV52YIsM9wBFlXUQFHheibRv1w5-tc7IkDzdhyuTnwsFc6mdllJLAsVaC1v0ryA74BhQSNc6nOosQ9UMvxrLAjEeiHkK78nO5gCvJZ5Ood16aro_knRCr2kok_GxSsXyTRpigz2mlfstMj91buxXSbHFGcOgy-eC3Fo3qKrRlpJnO4_AycLAgD0NL9vOAmyHZSYOQvZakSiSheNDfWFxKgjB023Clr2mFJ1MAdnxnVg_uvk3jQ6AZiaFulMz9w7yjVVM9brGAxF6O393bPQO9WqCdSrvg7swUG4yk1QlmfpK74sog8fXvCyKoJa2nkVIUsvhUxe5wve-M4ZKQvhSy1xHL8OWfWizd3z2Nu8HjHajAFGM60Wsv9lM_nPSqbXj4Xp7LXjIh0FQbjR4Ml3uUc1MhteqppgXrU2tvLgO0-PajwLEQIpT-tWZib8lcplQlXrlBCVPu0-LS7A8puEvZJV31Ylc7E5UfCk_mAaOYQwEEqHGTVbFpdgYsfK2