Additivity();\\n            this.previousAppenders = appenders(this.log4jLogger);\\n            this.appender = new RecordingAppender();\\n\\n            this.log4jLogger.removeAllAppenders();\\n            this.log4jLogger.setAdditivity(false);\\n            this.log4jLogger.setLevel(Level.TRACE);\\n            this.log4jLogger.addAppender(this.appender);\\n            this.logger = (LocationAwareLogger) LoggerFactory.getLogger(loggerName);\\n        }\\n\\n        private static TestLoggerContext create(String loggerName) {\\n            return new TestLoggerContext(loggerName);\\n        }\\n\\n        private static List<Appender> appenders(Logger logger) {\\n            List<Appender> appenders = new ArrayList<>();\\n            Enumeration<?> existingAppenders = logger.getAllAppenders();\\n            while (existingAppenders.hasMoreElements()) {\\n                appenders.add((Appender) existingAppenders.nextElement());\\n            }\\n            return appenders;\\n        }\\n\\n        private LocationAwareLogger logger() {\\n            return this.logger;\\n        }\\n\\n        private List<LoggingEvent> events() {\\n            return List.copyOf(this.appender.events);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void close() {\\n            this.log4jLogger.removeAppender(this.appender);\\n            this.log4jLogger.removeAllAppenders();\\n            for (Appender previousAppender : this.previousAppenders) {\\n                this.log4jLogger.addAppender(previousAppender);\\n            }\\n            this.log4jLogger.setLevel(this.previousLevel);\\n            this.log4jLogger.setAdditivity(this.previousAdditivity);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class RecordingAppender extends AppenderSkeleton {\\n\\n        private final List<LoggingEvent> events = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected void append(LoggingEvent event) {\\n            this.events.add(event);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void close() {\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public boolean requiresLayout() {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class LocationAwareInvoker {\\n\\n        private static void logWarning(LocationAwareLogger logger, String message, Throwable throwable) {\\n            logger.log(null, LocationAwareInvoker.class.getName(), LocationAwareLogger.WARN_INT, message, null, throwable);\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\n1304:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Exploring logging with log4j**\\n\\nI need to use log4j's AppenderSkeleton and understand the exact log4j 1.2 API, especially the LoggingEvent class. I wonder if I should reset the logger repository to manage a named logger. In the Log4jLoggerFactory, the ROOT can be referenced by the name \\\"ROOT.\\\" Setting additivity to false will help avoid any side effects on the root. I'm considering whether to import slf4j Logger or use qualified log4j Logger because of potential conflicts with Java imports. It's tricky!\\n\\n**Importing and configuring loggers**\\n\\nI’ll start by importing the necessary classes: org.apache.log4j.Logger, org.slf4j.LoggerFactory, and org.slf4j.spi.LocationAwareLogger. When I call context.logger(), it gives me a LocationAwareLogger, which is promising!\\n\\nNext, I’ll create a LocationAwareLogger instance by casting it from LoggerFactory. However, I realize I need to deal with Enumeration<Appender> for getting log appenders since log4j might return a raw type. I’m thinking I should store it as a List<Appender>, and check if I need to activate options. Testing my methods will begin soon!\\n\\n**Improving dynamic access testing**\\n\\nI’m considering dynamic class access, possibly using a Class object, but not `Class.forName`. I wonder if adding a second test for disabled access could improve behavior, though I want to focus on dynamic access alone. Perhaps I should aim for high coverage in integration. The existing active adapter includes many methods, and the task is to improve coverage, especially regarding dynamic access, which is currently uncovered. I think I can create a broad test without making it too expansive.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0a0399cef038036a0169f570d3236c819f95a6cf562375f20d\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9XDh_duEcO_i8a0_EZNXvbYI1JWguU8LhMz7eHZdYK14hmxs_Ig_3PYhLXbiIC4YVFgi0_Ps8c6SR3nKP0k4wGU3D-yaMiWtxqFNS5FkPDNvmsUySD91tO_pxRDJW3HHG16xjsECCDa1GEUggLwRIoMXjAocMYmmg1l8jwh2aXHlbG0qIgAOjlvQFXxOYx4fQcJRaNQs5t0edRXntfIt9KRzOHJaLxfkRJEhn5zgs1zfHDw57Lo0zULYAkG3E68tdHY_W_60Vp36QH_c6kN86Eiv1RpIFCh4jYV4waj7A_umYHBMj_8XKM4OiSSNpQH0u-Nho6gXVVZI4mYTL8CCdWuBa8gu6FS-5RiQ8fy4KTSs-JEqqcxNhlIJKkb5Lzy_GFQqL2-TGHAReb6b4qeyBN51sNejdV3XiV2w2FHPvczLS2gF7rcu_ymh1WPps-AxA1NrlfDq4PGtm5-uVnYB3apywXY-Qvd7else136ucFPWZqkDeVrta4DxReB7vDMFJA65Msv1jxu9cmmilRsGWiXVMqyMInW53wyYaLJ5On-MvMcJsX2WQz4ziczG1Zw9Ysirxnxuz8o-s4Bc39IvWtPUMF4d1X5MIouQljIb-Fl4PAMk275hdxmBhpiMB4qdf2s1WYQPYcif4zUql9v1o4vGkMPF7q0q4op-GLj0SQZQPNWA652ybYJmkBxlKlqQnTSuYPtEh9m_VppSz3MfQrpMBWZ9J5mdK_MFbzLCCwIeMTLm8F2Rx365LuS6h2rneQiyCMK8fic_g7GT0x0y_eieroluTHdS6-a-BCAA6jj4ZuVRI6GCmwWUDHxXjw4dQhg0JuERYmNPNnRAEq970UfrrT1h199XBPbEio1PbYy1w7EW7WGSrrvtijPgMSeTDY2CfkE1dX6ZKPmO5VVH14qg2ed9EPQGLzd3eJG-su3UKMteTtgUXD4UJRinul4cBLtOjOJJTCyb0bhW8_sjN7OvFiTrbG0C6AUj-zlwVSu5RZinxKoqR2QDFovWEjkRIgdPOX8FXGbsHEba-lYd2_BwUzrmyWkX3R5sWBbAlYoGrsEn44P6pyPIlKVc-K53ItAZIuv4TlzfVg0oG_6suDS0BQMJArFANpA1fRGtQtENwF3oHhBfE7gSP_fboZILRynb6q0wRThDZQgrBN2ModSCqRPaTdsEcH4FYTQAEyqQ_7e4W4lR3Oayv2tJKi1QFxUxdkTs8hjdo-AMZ7LbxEl2jDnLIBynJn6EjX6eSmNdDiNP2qA073mfXQzGfphJMwu-AWwmCZx94y_zs0Tzt76BS20ktA8A7UYUhQS9yHKZVF9dQbHbb7SWIjSUviXQ_ivcoLo3-xWvRrYCpjKpotcItq-xmgPN5auTDy0vsCrarTCknsyZfSxhkvaoBRh-Cz5VheCiEymWXPFmoMBN_eYtGqWKmUVtsDR1rRqN_E1BpT4oVslTMIGpglkRbJ94aX6nE51tqi8p1ZzPaxWAxLRs0kVt-CtfRwRM7p7FMZoMhWjB7UTpRZF4nRQuT5